apps/api/src/sportbook/actions/transactions/helper/helper.ts

ADAPTED_EVO_EXCEPTION
Default value : (code: string): never => { switch (code) { case ApiCode.ACCOUNTING_BALANCE_INSUFFICIENT.code: throw new SportsbookException(SportsbookErrors.decline_lowbalance); case ApiCode.ACCOUNTING_TRANSACTION_ALREADY_EXISTS.code: throw new SportsbookException( SportsbookErrors.invalid_request, ApiCode.ACCOUNTING_TRANSACTION_ALREADY_EXISTS.message, ); case ApiCode.USER_NOT_FOUND.code: throw new SportsbookException(SportsbookErrors.user_not_found); case ApiCode.BET_IS_NOT_FOUND.code: case ApiCode.BET_NOT_FOUND.code: case ApiCode.BET_ALREADY_EXISTS.code: throw new SportsbookException(SportsbookErrors.general_error); case ApiCode.BET_GR8_NOT_FOUND.code: throw new SportsbookException(SportsbookErrors.transaction_not_found); case ApiCode.BET_RESETTLE_ERROR.code: throw new SportsbookException(SportsbookErrors.decline_balance_conflict); default: throw new SportsbookException(SportsbookErrors.general_error); } }

apps/api/src/casino/slots/providers/pm8/system/helper/exception.helper.ts

ADAPTED_PM8_EXCEPTION
Default value : (code: string, message: string = ''): never => { switch (code) { case ApiCode.ACCOUNTING_BALANCE_INSUFFICIENT.code: throw new Pm8Exception(Pm8Errors.INSUFFICIENT_BALANCE); case ApiCode.ACCOUNTING_TRANSACTION_ALREADY_EXISTS.code: throw new Pm8Exception(Pm8Errors.SYSTEM_UNEXPECTED); case ApiCode.USER_NOT_FOUND.code: throw new Pm8Exception(Pm8Errors.PLAYER_NOT_FOUND); case ApiCode.NOT_FOUND.code: case ApiCode.BET_RESTRICTED_BY_PROMO_ACTIVE_CODE.code: throw new Pm8Exception(Pm8Errors.VALIDATION_FAILED, message); case ApiCode.BET_IS_NOT_FOUND.code: case ApiCode.BET_NOT_FOUND.code: case ApiCode.BET_ALREADY_EXISTS.code: case ApiCode.ACCOUNTING_TRANSACTION_NOT_FOUND.code: throw new Pm8Exception(Pm8Errors.TARGET_TX_NOT_FOUND); case ApiCode.BET_RESETTLE_ERROR.code: throw new Pm8Exception(Pm8Errors.INSUFFICIENT_BALANCE); default: throw new Pm8Exception(Pm8Errors.SYSTEM_UNEXPECTED); } }

seedOneStreamer
Default value : async (args: { username: string; password: string; }) => { const affiliateCodes = affiliateCodesForStreamer.map((code) => ({ id: `${args.username}-${code}`, })); const streamer = await prisma.user.upsert({ where: { username: args.username, }, create: { username: args.username, password: args.password, email: `${args.username}@example.com`, emailVerified: true, avatar: '/assets/avatars/user/1.png', isStreamer: true, roles: { create: { role: 'User', }, }, affiliateCodes: { createMany: { data: affiliateCodes, }, }, statsUsd: { create: { totalWithdraws: 100, }, }, }, update: {}, }); let i = 0; for (const tag of adminTipsTags) { const id = Number(`${streamer.id}000${i++}`); const amount = getRandomFromArray(depositAmountArray); await prisma.adminTips.upsert({ where: { id, }, create: { id, recipientId: streamer.id, senderId: streamer.id, type: 'ADD_BALANCE', amount, usdAmount: amount, currencyId: 'EVO', notes: 'ku ku', transactionId: randomUUID(), tag, }, update: {}, }); } for (let j = 0; j < getRandomInt(2, 5); j++) { const referralUsername = referralsUsernames[j]; const amount = getRandomFromArray(depositAmountArray); const username = `${referralUsername}-${streamer.id}`; await prisma.user.upsert({ where: { username, }, create: { username, password: args.password, email: `${username}@example.com`, emailVerified: true, avatar: '/assets/avatars/user/1.png', roles: { create: { role: 'User', }, }, affiliateCodeId: getRandomFromArray(affiliateCodes).id, statsUsd: { create: { totalDeposits: amount, ltv: amount, totalLoss: amount, totalWagered: amount, }, }, userBalance: { create: { currencyId: CurrencySymbol.DBC, amount: '1000', vaultAmount: '1000', }, }, }, update: {}, }); } }

Type : Array<AffiliateLevel>

findAffiliateLevel
Default value : (wageredUsdAmount: Decimal) => { const level = AFFILIATE_LEVELS.findLast((level) => wageredUsdAmount.gte(level.minWageredUsdAmount), ); if (!level) { throw new ApiException( ApiCode.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, `Affiliate level not found for wagered usd amount: ${wageredUsdAmount}`, ); } return level; }
getAffiliateLevelById
Default value : (id: number) => { return AFFILIATE_LEVELS.find((level) => level.id === id) ?? null; }
getAffiliateLevelByIdOrThrow
Default value : (id: number) => { const level = getAffiliateLevelById(id); if (!level) { throw new ApiException( ApiCode.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, `Affiliate level not found for id: ${id}`, ); } return level; }

libs/shared/src/common/utils/utils.ts

ALPHANUMERIC_CHARS
Type : object
Default value : { upper: 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789', lower: 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789', mixed: 'ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789', }
calculatePercentageChange
Default value : ( current: number, previous: number, ): number => { if (current === 0 && previous === 0) { return 0; } if (previous === 0) { return current > 0 ? 100 : -100; } if ((previous < 0 && current >= 0) || (previous > 0 && current <= 0)) { return ((current - previous) / Math.abs(previous)) * 100; } return ((current - previous) / Math.abs(previous)) * 100; }

Default value : /^[A-Za-z0-9]+$/
ENGLISH_LOWERCASE_LETTERS_NUMBERS_REGEX

parseExpiryDuration
Default value : (duration: string): number => { const unit = duration.slice(-1); const value = parseInt(duration.slice(0, -1), 10); let milliseconds; switch (unit) { case 'd': // Days milliseconds = value * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000; break; case 'h': // Hours milliseconds = value * 60 * 60 * 1000; break; case 'm': // Minutes milliseconds = value * 60 * 1000; break; case 's': // Seconds milliseconds = value * 1000; break; default: // Default to 1 hour if unable to parse milliseconds = 3600000; } return milliseconds; }
rawSeed
Default value : (...args: string[]) => { return args.join(':'); }

skewHigh
Default value : (lo: number, hi: number, p = 2): number => { const t = Math.pow(Math.random(), p); return Math.round(hi - t * (hi - lo)); }
skewLow
Default value : (lo: number, hi: number, p = 2): number => { const t = Math.pow(Math.random(), p); return Math.round(lo + t * (hi - lo)); }

Type : Record<string, PickFn>
Default value : { FIRST_STEP: () => 1, RANDOM_FULL: (_d, m) => randInt(1, m), LOW_AGGRO: (_d, m) => skewLow(1, Math.floor(m / 3)), MID_AGGRO: (_d, m) => randInt(Math.round(m / 6), Math.floor(m / 2)), HIGH_AGGRO: (_d, m) => skewHigh(Math.floor(m / 2), m), LOTTERY_MIX: (_d, m) => { const r = Math.random(); if (r < 0.7) return STRATS.LOW_AGGRO(_d, m); if (r < 0.9) return STRATS.MID_AGGRO(_d, m); return STRATS.HIGH_AGGRO(_d, m); }, RANDOM_LUCKY: (d, m) => (d > 1 ? randInt(1, Math.min(d - 1, m)) : 1), }

apps/api/src/dashboard-v2/repository/common.sql.ts

betsSql
Default value : (args: GameQueryArgs) => Prisma.sql` SELECT DISTINCT on (b.id) b.id, b.user_id, b.usd_amount, b.usd_payout, b.settled_at, gi.provider_id as provider_id, gi.id as game_id, gi.slug as slug, gi.name as game_name, gi.type as type, r.instant_total_claimed, r.daily_total_claimed, r.weekly_total_claimed, r.monthly_total_claimed FROM bet b INNER JOIN "public"."user" u ON b.user_id = u.id LEFT JOIN game_identity gi ON b.game_id = gi.id LEFT JOIN game_in_category gic ON gi.id = gic.game_id LEFT JOIN rakeback r ON b.user_id = r.user_id ${args.providerSlugs ? Prisma.sql`LEFT JOIN game_provider gp ON gi.provider_id = gp.id` : Prisma.sql``} WHERE b.settled_at BETWEEN ${args.start}::timestamp AND ${args.end}::timestamp AND u.id IS NOT NULL AND b.status = 'SETTLED'::bet_status ${args.gameCategory ? Prisma.sql`AND gic.category = ${args.gameCategory}::game_category` : Prisma.sql``} ${args.gameSlug ? Prisma.sql`AND gi.slug = ${args.gameSlug}` : Prisma.sql``} ${args.gameName ? Prisma.sql`AND gi.name ILIKE ${'%' + args.gameName + '%'}` : Prisma.sql``} ${args.providerSlugs ? Prisma.sql`AND gp.slug = ANY(ARRAY(SELECT json_array_elements_text(${args.providerSlugs}::json))::text[])` : Prisma.sql``} AND ${isInStatsSql()} `
formatDecimals
Default value : (result: Record<string, unknown>[]) => { const DECIMAL_PART = 4; for (const row of result) { for (const key in row) { const value = row[key]; if ( typeof value === 'number' || typeof value === 'bigint' || value instanceof Decimal ) { row[key] = Number(new Decimal(value.toString()).toFixed(DECIMAL_PART)); } } } }
isInStatsSql
Default value : () => Prisma.sql` u.is_staff = false AND u.is_streamer = false AND u.is_youtuber = false ${FS.isEnabled('show_test_users_in_dashboard') ? Prisma.sql`` : Prisma.sql`AND u.is_test = false`} `
logTable
Default value : ( name: string, query: unknown, result: Record<string, unknown>[], ) => { console.log(`${name} ${result.length} rows`, query); console.table(result); }
selectAnalyticsSql
Default value : (args: GameQueryArgs) => Prisma.sql` COALESCE(COUNT(DISTINCT b.user_id), 0) as active_players, COUNT(b.id) as bet_count, SUM(b.usd_amount) as turnover, SUM(b.usd_amount) - SUM(b.usd_payout) as ggr, SUM(b.usd_amount) / NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT b.user_id), 0) as atpu, (SUM(b.usd_amount) - SUM(b.usd_payout)) / NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT b.user_id), 0) as arpu, (SUM(b.usd_amount) - SUM(b.usd_payout)) / NULLIF(SUM(b.usd_amount), 0) * 100 as margin, COUNT(b.id) / NULLIF(COUNT(DISTINCT b.user_id), 0) as abcpu, AVG(b.usd_amount) as average_bet_amount, SUM(b.usd_amount) - SUM(b.usd_payout) - COALESCE( SUM(b.instant_total_claimed) + SUM(b.daily_total_claimed) + SUM(b.weekly_total_claimed) + SUM(b.monthly_total_claimed), 0 ) as ngr `
seriesSql
Default value : (args: TimeQueryArgs) => Prisma.sql` WITH series_start as ( SELECT generate_series( ${args.start}::timestamp, ${args.end}::timestamp, ${'1 ' + args.timeGroup}::interval ) AS date ) SELECT date::timestamp as start, date::timestamp + ${'1 ' + args.timeGroup}::interval as end, ${SeriesType.range} as series FROM series_start WHERE (date::timestamp + ${'1 ' + args.timeGroup}::interval) <= ${args.end}::timestamp UNION SELECT ${args.start}::timestamp as start, ${args.end}::timestamp as end, ${SeriesType.all} as series ORDER BY series, start `

libs/shared/src/api/serialization/currency/currency.transformer.ts

bigIntToDecimalString
Default value : (bigIntValue: bigint, digits: number) => { const stringValue = bigIntValue.toString().padStart(digits + 1, '0'); const integerPart = stringValue.slice(0, -digits) || '0'; const decimalPart = stringValue.slice(-digits); const trimmedDecimalPart = decimalPart.replace(/0+$/, ''); if (trimmedDecimalPart === '') { return integerPart; } return `${integerPart}.${trimmedDecimalPart}`; }
decimalStringToBigInt
Default value : ( decimalString: string, digits: number, ) => { const [integerPart, decimalPart = ''] = decimalString.split('.'); const paddedDecimal = decimalPart.padEnd(digits, '0'); return BigInt(integerPart + paddedDecimal.slice(0, digits)); }

Default value : (currencyId: CurrencySymbol) => CURRENCY_INFO[currencyId].digits

Default value : ( transactions: BetSlotTransactionDto[], ): TransactionResponseDto[] => { return ( transactions?.map((tx) => ({ action_id: tx.external_action_id ?? tx.id, tx_id: tx.id, processed_at: formatIsoDate(tx.updatedAt ?? tx.createdAt), })) ?? [] ); }

buildSlotUserId
Default value : ( userId: string, currency: CurrencySymbol, ): string => { return `${userId}-${currency}`; }
compareRequestSignatureHmacSha256
Default value : ( rawBody: Buffer | string, expectedSignature: string, authToken: string, ) => { const actualSignature = createSignatureHmacSha256(rawBody, authToken); return actualSignature === expectedSignature; }
createSignatureHmacSha256
Default value : ( rawBody: Buffer | string, authToken: string, ) => crypto.createHmac('sha256', authToken).update(rawBody).digest('hex')
formatIsoDate
Default value : (date: Date) => { return date.toISOString(); }
parseEvoSession
Default value : (args: CommonRequestDto): SlotUserSession => { if (args.game_id === EvoGamesSlug.BLACKJACK) { const [userId, currency] = args.user_id.split('-'); return { userId: parseInt(userId), currency: currency as CurrencySymbol }; } return { userId: parseInt(args.user_id), currency: args.currency as CurrencySymbol, }; }

apps/api/src/casino/house/mines/utils/index.ts

calculateMultiplier
Default value : ( board: HouseGameMinesBoard<'private'>, config: MinesConfigResponseDto, ): { currentMultiplier: number; nextMultiplier: number } => { let currentMultiplier = 1.0; let nextMultiplier = 1.0; const { openedCellsCount, gridCellsCount, bombsCount } = board; for (let i = 0; i < openedCellsCount; i++) { currentMultiplier *= (gridCellsCount - i) / (gridCellsCount - bombsCount - i); } currentMultiplier = currentMultiplier * config.rtp; for (let i = 0; i < openedCellsCount + 1; i++) { nextMultiplier *= (gridCellsCount - i) / (gridCellsCount - bombsCount - i); } nextMultiplier = nextMultiplier * config.rtp; return { currentMultiplier, nextMultiplier }; }
generateBoard
Default value : ( gridCellsCount: number, bombsCount: number, betAmount: Decimal, currencyId: CurrencySymbol, seed: UserFairnessSeedsDto, ): HouseGameMinesBoard<'private'> => { const cells = Array.from({ length: gridCellsCount }, (_, i) => i); const minePositions = RngGames.getRandomMines({ serverSeed: seed.serverSeed, clientSeed: seed.clientSeed, nonce: seed.nonce, bombsCount, gridCellsCount, }); const board: HouseGameMinesBoard<'private'> = { cells: {}, gridCellsCount, bombsCount, openedCellsCount: 0, betInfo: { amount: betAmount, currencyId, seed, }, }; for (let i = 0; i < cells.length; i++) { board.cells[i] = { isOpen: false, hasMine: minePositions.includes(i), }; } return board; }
getPublicBoard
Default value : ( board: HouseGameMinesBoard<'private'>, ): HouseGameMinesBoard<'public'> => { return { cells: Object.entries(board.cells).reduce( (acc, [position, cell]) => { acc[position] = { isOpen: cell.isOpen, }; return acc; }, {} as HouseGameMinesBoard<'public'>['cells'], ), openedCellsCount: board.openedCellsCount, gridCellsCount: board.gridCellsCount, bombsCount: board.bombsCount, betInfo: { amount: board.betInfo.amount, currencyId: board.betInfo.currencyId, seed: board.betInfo.seed, }, }; }

apps/api/src/casino/house/keno/keno.utils.ts

calculateMultipliers
Default value : ( rtp: number = 1, ): Record<KenoRisk, Record<number, number[]>> => { if (rtp !== 0 && rtp > 0) { rtp = rtp + 0.01; //default multipliers from shuffle, have 0.99 rtp } if (rtp < 0 || rtp >= 1.0) { return KENO_MULTIPLIERS; } const result: Record<KenoRisk, Record<number, number[]>> = { [KenoRisk.CLASSIC]: {}, [KenoRisk.LOW]: {}, [KenoRisk.MEDIUM]: {}, [KenoRisk.HIGH]: {}, }; Object.entries(KENO_MULTIPLIERS).forEach(([risk, riskTable]) => { result[risk as KenoRisk] = {}; Object.entries(riskTable).forEach(([numbersSelected, multipliers]) => { result[risk as KenoRisk][Number(numbersSelected)] = multipliers.map( (val) => Number((val * rtp).toFixed(2)), ); }); }); return result; }

compareSignatureHmacSha256
Default value : ( rawBody: Buffer | string, authToken: string, expectedSignature: string | null, ) => { return ( expectedSignature && expectedSignature === signWithHmacSha256(rawBody, authToken) ); }
signWithHmacSha256

compareSignatureHmacSha512
Default value : ( rawBody: Buffer | string, authToken: string, expectedSignature: string, ) => { const actualSignature = crypto .createHmac('sha512', authToken) .update(rawBody) .digest('hex'); return actualSignature === expectedSignature; }

libs/shared/src/basic/base.main.ts

createNestApp
Default value : async (options: MainOptions) => { const opts = mergeDefault(options); const app = await NestFactory.create(options.appModule, { bodyParser: true, rawBody: true, forceCloseConnections: true, }); const configService = app.get(ConfigService); app.connectMicroservice<MicroserviceOptions>( { transport: Transport.REDIS, options: opts.rpc.redisOptions, }, { inheritAppConfig: opts.rpc.inheritAppConfig, }, ); const { httpAdapter } = app.get(HttpAdapterHost); app.useGlobalFilters( ...opts.globalFiltersWithHttpAdapter.map((factory) => factory(httpAdapter)), ...opts.globalFilters.map((factory) => factory()), ); app.useGlobalInterceptors( ...opts.globalInterceptors.map((factory) => factory()), ); if (opts.isSentryEnabled) { app.useGlobalFilters(new SentryFilter(httpAdapter)); } if (opts.http.cors) { app.enableCors({ origin: opts.http.cors, credentials: true, }); } app.useGlobalPipes( new ValidationPipe({ enableDebugMessages: true, transform: true, whitelist: true, // DO NOT REMOVE! With no whitelisted fields hackers can set any user data. }), ); app.use(cookieParser()); // cookie parser middleware if (opts.usePassport) { const SESSION_SECRET = configService.get('SESSION_SECRET') ?? '0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz'; app.use( session({ secret: SESSION_SECRET, resave: true, saveUninitialized: true, cookie: { secure: !isLocal, httpOnly: true, }, }), ); app.use(passport.initialize()); app.use(passport.session()); } app.useLogger(app.get(WINSTON_MODULE_NEST_PROVIDER)); if (opts.swagger?.code) { buildSwagger({ app, service: opts.swagger.code }); } app.enableShutdownHooks(); return app; }

Default value : async () => { try { for (const icon of CUSTOM_ICONS) { const game = await prisma.gameIdentity.findUnique({ where: { originalSlug: icon.originalSlug, }, }); if (!game || game.images?.imageUrl === icon.imageUrl) { continue; } await prisma.gameIdentity.update({ where: { originalSlug: icon.originalSlug, }, data: { images: { imageUrl: icon.imageUrl, }, }, }); } } catch (error) { console.error('seedCustomIcons', error); } }

libs/_prisma/src/extension/decimal-json.extension.ts

decimalJsonExtension
Type : Prisma.Middleware
Default value : async (params, next) => { if (isMutation(params.action)) { const model = Prisma.dmmf.datamodel.models.find( (m) => m.name === params.model, ); if (!model) return next(params); const serializeDecimalInJson = <T extends Record<string, unknown>>( data: T | null, fields: PrismaField[], ): T | null => { if (!data) return data; const jsonFields = fields.filter((f) => f.type === 'Json'); const result = { ...data } as Record<string, unknown>; for (const field of jsonFields) { const fieldValue = result[field.name]; if (!fieldValue) continue; if (typeof fieldValue === 'object') { result[field.name] = serializeDecimal(fieldValue); } } return result as T; }; params.args.data = serializeDecimalInJson(params.args.data, [ ...model.fields, ]); } const result = await next(params); if (isQuery(params.action)) { const model = Prisma.dmmf.datamodel.models.find( (m) => m.name === params.model, ); if (!model) return result; const deserializeDecimalInJson = <T extends Record<string, unknown>>( data: T | null, fields: PrismaField[], ): T | null => { if (!data) return data; const jsonFields = fields.filter((f) => f.type === 'Json'); const result = { ...data } as Record<string, unknown>; for (const field of jsonFields) { const fieldValue = result[field.name]; if (!fieldValue) continue; if (typeof fieldValue === 'object') { result[field.name] = deserializeDecimal(fieldValue); } } return result as T; }; if (Array.isArray(result)) { return result.map((item) => deserializeDecimalInJson(item, [...model.fields]), ); } return deserializeDecimalInJson(result, [...model.fields]); } return result; }
deserializeDecimal
Default value : <T>( obj: T, ): T | Decimal | Array<T> | Record<string, unknown> => { if ( typeof obj === 'object' && obj !== null && obj.constructor !== Object && obj.constructor !== Array ) { return obj; } if (typeof obj === 'string') { if (/^\d+\.\d+$/.test(obj)) { return new DecimalScalar(obj); } } if (Array.isArray(obj)) { return obj.map((item) => deserializeDecimal(item)); } if (typeof obj === 'object' && obj !== null) { const result: Record<string, unknown> = {}; Object.entries(obj as Record<string, unknown>).forEach(([key, value]) => { result[key] = deserializeDecimal(value); }); return result; } return obj; }
isMutation
Default value : (action: Prisma.PrismaAction) => action === 'create' || action === 'createMany' || action === 'createManyAndReturn' || action === 'update' || action === 'updateMany' || action === 'updateManyAndReturn' || action === 'upsert'
isQuery
Default value : (action: Prisma.PrismaAction) => action === 'findUnique' || action === 'findUniqueOrThrow' || action === 'findMany' || action === 'findFirst' || action === 'findFirstOrThrow' || action === 'aggregate' || action === 'groupBy' || action === 'createManyAndReturn' || action === 'updateManyAndReturn'
serializeDecimal
Default value : <T>( obj: T, ): T | string | Array<T> | Record<string, unknown> => { if (obj instanceof Prisma.Decimal) { const stringValue = obj.toString(); return stringValue.includes('.') ? stringValue : `${stringValue}.0`; } if (Array.isArray(obj)) { return obj.map((item) => serializeDecimal(item)); } if (typeof obj === 'object' && obj !== null) { const result: Record<string, unknown> = {}; Object.entries(obj as Record<string, unknown>).forEach(([key, value]) => { result[key] = serializeDecimal(value); }); return result; } return obj; }

Type : SlotRndGenerator.PayTableEntry[]
Default value : ranges.flatMap( (cfg, idx) => { const { min, max, step, weightPercent } = cfg; const values: number[] = []; if (min === max) { values.push(min); } else { for (let v = min; v < max; v = parseFloat((v + step).toFixed(2))) { values.push(parseFloat(v.toFixed(2))); } if (idx === ranges.length - 1) { values.push(parseFloat(max.toFixed(2))); } } const totalWeight = weightPercent * WEIGHT_SCALE; const baseWeight = Math.floor(totalWeight / values.length); let remainder = totalWeight - baseWeight * values.length; return values.map((multiplier) => { const weight = baseWeight + (remainder-- > 0 ? 1 : 0); return { multiplier, weight }; }); }, )

libs/shared/src/common/decorators/retry/retry.ts

defaultRetryOptions
Type : RetryOptions
Default value : { retryCount: 3, retryTimeout: 200, retrySuccessPredicate: () => false, retryFailPredicate: () => true, }
retry
Default value : <T>( cb: () => Promise<T>, retryOptions?: Partial<RetryOptions>, ): Promise<T> => { const options: RetryOptions = { ...defaultRetryOptions, ...retryOptions, }; let count = 0; return new Promise<T>((resolve, reject) => { const run = async () => { count++; try { const data = await cb(); if (options.retrySuccessPredicate(data)) { throw data; } resolve(data); } catch (error: unknown) { if (count > options!.retryCount) { reject(error); } else if (options.retryFailPredicate(error)) { const timeout = typeof options!.retryTimeout === 'function' ? options!.retryTimeout(count) : options!.retryTimeout; setTimeout(run, timeout); } else { reject(error); } } }; void run(); }); }

libs/ws-throttler/src/utils.ts

extractIP
Default value : ( xForwardedFor: string | string[] | undefined, ): string | null => { if (!xForwardedFor) { return null; } if (typeof xForwardedFor === 'string') { return xForwardedFor.split(',').map((ip) => ip.trim())[0]; } if (Array.isArray(xForwardedFor) && xForwardedFor.length > 0) { return xForwardedFor[0]; } throw new BadRequestException('Invalid x-forwarded-for header'); }
getIpFromClient
Default value : (client: Socket): string => { const xForwardedFor = client.handshake.headers?.['x-forwarded-for']; const ip = client.handshake.headers?.['cf-connecting-ip']?.toString() || extractIP(xForwardedFor) || client.handshake.address || client.conn.remoteAddress; if (!ip) { EvoLogger.error('getIpFromClient', 'Could not determine client IP address'); throw new BadRequestException('Could not determine client IP address'); } const { isValid } = validateIP(ip); if (!isValid) { EvoLogger.error('getIpFromClient', `Invalid IP address: ${ip}`); throw new BadRequestException(`Invalid IP address: ${ip}`); } return ip; }
validateIP
Default value : (ip: string): { isValid: boolean; version: string } => { const version = isIP(ip); // 0 (invalid), 4 (IPv4), 6 (IPv6) return { isValid: version === 4 || version === 6, version: version === 4 ? 'IPv4' : version === 6 ? 'IPv6' : 'Invalid', }; }

extractLoggerContext
Default value : (req: RequestExt) => { return { user: { id: req.user?.id, username: req.user?.username, sId: req.user?.sId, }, ip: req.ip, }; }
getLoggerContext
Default value : () => { const request = ClsServiceManager.getClsService().get<RequestExt | undefined>( EVO_CLS_REQ, ); if (!request) { return undefined; } return extractLoggerContext(request); }

apps/api/src/auth/guards/feature-enabled.guard.ts

FeatureEnabledGuard
Default value : ( featureFlag: keyof typeof FeatureFlags, options: { readUser?: boolean; } = { readUser: true, }, ) => { @Injectable() class FeatureEnabledGuard extends AuthGuard('jwt') implements CanActivate { constructor() { super(); } async canActivate(context: ExecutionContext): Promise<boolean> { let user: RequestUser | undefined; try { if (options?.readUser) { await super.canActivate(context); const request = context.switchToHttp().getRequest(); user = request?.user as RequestUser; } } catch (e) { if (!(e instanceof UnauthorizedException)) { EvoLogger.error( FeatureEnabledGuard, 'Failed to activate feature enabled guard:', e, ); } } if (FS.isEnabled(featureFlag, user)) { return true; } throw new NotFoundException(); } } return FeatureEnabledGuard; }

Default value : (query: TimeQuery): TimeQueryArgs => { if (!query.timeGroup) { throw new ApiException(ApiCode.BAD_REQUEST, 'timeGroup is required'); } if (query.startDate && query.endDate) { return { start: query.startDate, end: query.endDate, timeGroup: query.timeGroup, }; } else if (query.timeRange) { const timeRangeConfig = TimeRangeConfig[query.timeRange]; const now = DateTime.utc(); return { start: timeRangeConfig.start(now).toJSDate(), end: timeRangeConfig.end(now).toJSDate(), timeGroup: query.timeGroup, }; } throw new ApiException( ApiCode.BAD_REQUEST, 'timeRange or timeRangeCustom is required', ); }

Default value : () => { return ( target: object, propertyKey: string, descriptor: PropertyDescriptor, ) => { const originalMethod = descriptor.value; descriptor.value = async function ( ctx: CommandContext<Context>, ...args: unknown[] ) { try { return await originalMethod.call(this, ctx, ...args); } catch (error) { if (error instanceof ApiException) { await ctx.reply(error.apiCode.message); } else if (error instanceof Error) { await ctx.reply(error.message); } EvoLogger.error( HandleApiException, 'Error on callback action telegram bot', error, ); } }; return descriptor; }; }

isBatchValid

libs/shared/src/api/validators/isDecimal.ts

makeDeserializeDecimal
Default value : (args: { isOptional: boolean }) => { const { isOptional } = args; return (args: TransformFnParams) => { if (isOptional && args.value === undefined) { return undefined; } if (isOptional && args.value === null) { return null; } if (args.value instanceof Decimal) { return args.value; } if (typeof args.value !== 'string') { throw new ApiException( ApiCode.BAD_REQUEST, `Type of the ${args.key} is a ${typeof args.value}, but it should be a string`, ); } try { return new Decimal(args.value); } catch (error) { if ( error instanceof Error && error.message.startsWith('[DecimalError] Invalid argument: ') ) { throw new ApiException( ApiCode.BAD_REQUEST, `${args.key} (${args.value}) is not a valid decimal number`, ); } throw error; } }; }

apps/api/src/auth/guards/permission.guard.ts

PermissionGuard
Default value : (...permissionKeys: PermissionKey[]) => { @Injectable() class PermissionGuard extends AuthGuard('jwt') implements CanActivate { constructor(public readonly userService: UserService) { super(); } async canActivate(context: ExecutionContext) { await super.canActivate(context); const request = context.switchToHttp().getRequest(); const user = request.user as RequestUser; if (user.roles.some((role) => role.role === Role.SuperAdmin)) { return true; } const hasPermission = user.permissions.some((permission) => permissionKeys.includes(permission.permissionKey as PermissionKey), ); if (!hasPermission) { throw new ApiException(ApiCode.INSUFFICIENT_PERMISSIONS); } if (FS.isEnabled('disable_otp', user)) { return true; } if (!user.mfaSecret) { throw new ApiException(ApiCode.USER_MFA_NOT_ENABLED); } return true; } } return PermissionGuard; }

Pm8IdempotencyResponse
Default value : <T>(options: Pm8IdempotencyOptions<T>) => { return (target: object, propertyKey: string, descriptor: PropertyDescriptor) => { const originalMethod = descriptor.value; descriptor.value = async function (...args: T[]) { const cacheManager = Pm8CacheManager.getInstance().getCacheManager(); const payload = args[options.payloadIndex ?? 0]; const key = options.key(payload) const cachedResult = await cacheManager.get(key); if (cachedResult) { if (!cachedResult?.tx) { return await originalMethod.apply(this, args); } cachedResult.tx.processed = true; return cachedResult; } const result = await originalMethod.apply(this, args); await cacheManager.set(key, result, options.ttl ?? 3600); return result; }; return descriptor; }; }

apps/api/src/auth/session/utils.ts

sortSession
Default value : (sessions: UserSessionDto[]) => { const currentSessions = sessions.filter((el) => el.isCurrent); const activeSessions = sessions.filter((el) => !el.isCurrent && el.isActive); const otherSessions = sessions.filter((el) => !el.isCurrent && !el.isActive); const sortedCurrent = currentSessions.sort( (a, b) => b.lastActivity.getTime() - a.lastActivity.getTime(), ); const sortedActive = activeSessions.sort( (a, b) => b.lastActivity.getTime() - a.lastActivity.getTime(), ); const sortedOthers = otherSessions.sort( (a, b) => b.lastActivity.getTime() - a.lastActivity.getTime(), ); const finalData = [...sortedCurrent, ...sortedActive, ...sortedOthers]; return finalData; }

validateAndHashPassword

libs/_prisma/src/error/wrap-prisma-error.decorator.ts

WrapPrismaError
Default value : ( apiCodeOrOpts: ApiCodeEntry | WrapPrismaErrorOptions, ...prismaCodes: PrismaErrorCode[] ) => { return ( target: object, propertyKey: string | symbol, descriptor: PropertyDescriptor, ) => { const opts = ( 'apiCode' in apiCodeOrOpts ? apiCodeOrOpts : { apiCode: apiCodeOrOpts, log: false } ) as WrapPrismaErrorOptions; const originalMethod = descriptor.value; const targetName = target.constructor.name; descriptor.value = async function (...args: unknown[]) { try { return await originalMethod.apply(this, args); } catch (error) { if (prismaCodes.some((code) => PrismaErrorUtils.isKnown(error, code))) { if (opts.log) { EvoLogger.error(targetName, `Prisma error`, error); } throw new ApiException(opts.apiCode); } throw error; } }; }; }
